revision.text:
'''Bondeson Glacier''' ({{Coord|82|44|S|165|0|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] about {{convert|7|nmi|km}} long, flowing north along the east side of [[Benson Ridge]] into the lower portion of [[Robb Glacier]]. It was mapped by the [[United States Geological Survey]] from tellurometer surveys (1961–62) and from Navy air photos (1960), and named by the [[Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names]] for [[W. Bondeson]], Master of the [[USNS Private John R. Towle (T-AK-240)|USNS ''Private John R. Towle'']] during [[U.S. Navy Operation Deepfreeze]] 1964 and 1965.<ref name=gnis/>

