'''Dominique C. Bergmann''' is a [[plant scientist]] working on [[Cellular differentiation|cell differentiation]], [[stem cell]] renewal, and [[cell polarity]] with a focus on [[guard cell]] development as a model for all three cellular behaviors.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.the-scientist.com/?articles.view/articleNo/30580/title/Dominique-Bergmann--Probing-Plant-Pores/|title=Dominique Bergmann: Probing Plant Pores {{!}} The Scientist Magazine®|website=The Scientist|access-date=2016-07-11}}</ref> She is a professor at [[Stanford University]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://med.stanford.edu/profiles/dominique-bergmann|title=Dominique Bergmann {{!}} Stanford Medicine Profiles|website=med.stanford.edu|access-date=2016-07-11}}</ref>
Her lab has a website with more information about her research program.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.stanford.edu/group/bergmann/cgi-bin/bergmannlab/home|title=WELCOME {{!}} BERGMANN LAB|website=www.stanford.edu|access-date=2016-07-11}}</ref> For the last several years she has been a [[Gordon and Betty Moore Foundation|Gordon and Betty Moore]] HHMI funded researcher.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Powell|first=Kendall|date=2014-12-22|title=Dominique Bergmann: Passionate about plant polarity|url=http://jcb.rupress.org/content/207/6/680|journal=The Journal of Cell Biology|language=en|volume=207|issue=6|pages=680–681|doi=10.1083/jcb.2076pi|issn=0021-9525|pmc=4274260|pmid=25533841}}</ref>
== Awards and honors == Bergmann won the [[American Society of Plant Biologists]]' [[Charles Schull Award]] in 2010.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aspb.org/awards-funding/aspb-awards/charles-albert-shull-award/#tab-id-3|title=ASPB {{!}} Charles Albert Shull Award|website=www.aspb.org|access-date=2016-07-11}}</ref> She was elected to the National Academy of Sciences in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nasonline.org/news-and-multimedia/news/may-2-2017-NAS-Election.html?referrer=https://www.google.com/|title=National Academy of Sciences|last=|first=|date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-10-10}}</ref>
