An '''Isotropic beacon''' is a hypothetical type of [[beacon|transmission beacon]] that emits a uniform [[electromagnetism|EM]] signal in all directions for the purposes of [[communication with extraterrestrial intelligence]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4oxZgRn3QFYC|title=Communication with Extraterrestrial Intelligence (CETI)|last=Vakoch|first=Douglas A.|date=2011-04-01|publisher=[[SUNY Press]]|isbn=9781438437958|language=en}}</ref>

== Isotropic beacons and their relation to SETI ==
An isotropic beacon can be any transmitter that emits a uniform electromagnetic field. However, the term is most commonly used to describe a transmitter used by a civilization to call attention to itself over interstellar distances.{{cn|date=May 2018}} [[Project Cyclops]] is and was one of the first looks at the theoretical framework of what it would take to create such a device.{{cn|date=May 2018}}

