{{Infobox musical artist | name = Matt Lebofsky | background = solo_singer | birth_name = | alias = | birth_date = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | birth_place = | origin = | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date 1st) --> | death_place = | genre = Rock, Jazz | occupation = Musician, Computer Scientist | instrument = | years_active = ~1980–present | label = | associated_acts = [[Secret Chiefs 3]], [[miRthkon]], [[MoeTar]], Bodies Floating Ashore, Midline Errors, The Fuxedos, Research & Development, [[Faun Fables]], Fuzzy Cousins, [[Species Being]], [[Mumble & Peg]], JOB, Herb, Dropsy | website = http://lebofsky.com }}
'''Matt Lebofsky''' is an Oakland, California-based multi-instrumentalist and composer. Growing up in New York he studied piano/composition with [[Arthur Cunningham]] from 1978-1988. As a performer/composer he is currently active in several bands such as [[miRthkon]], [[MoeTar]], [[Secret Chiefs 3]], [http://www.bodiesfloatingashore.com Bodies Floating Ashore], [http://www.fuxedos.com The Fuxedos], [https://web.archive.org/web/20080518071328/http://www.threepiececombo.com/ Three Piece Combo], [http://www.researchanddevelopment.us Research & Development], [https://web.archive.org/web/20080517055806/http://www.midlineerrors.com/ Midline Errors], [http://www.fuzzycousins.com Fuzzy Cousins] and [http://www.feastorfamine.com/job JOB]. He is also a long-time prolific member of the [[Immersion Composition Society]] Origin Lodge. He toured nationally in 2006 as a member of [[Faun Fables]], and throughout 2000-2001 as a member of [[Species Being]], and released three albums and toured internationally with [http://www.lebofsky.com/music/mumble Mumble & Peg] from 1995-2002.
Matt is also a computer programmer, webmaster, and database/systems administrator at the [[Berkeley SETI Research Center]], working with [[Breakthrough Listen]] since 2015, and as a core member of the small staff developing/maintaining the world's largest distributed computing project [[SETI@home]] (since its inception at the University of California at Berkeley's [[Space Sciences Laboratory]] in 1997).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://arstechnica.com/uncategorized/2002/10/1145-2/|title=News of impeding Seti@Home death premature|last=Locklear|first=Fred|date=October 15, 2002|work=[[Ars Technica]]|accessdate=30 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=About SETI@home and Personnel|url=http://setiathome.berkeley.edu/sah_about.php|publisher=setiathome.berkeley.edu|accessdate=3 Jan 2012}}</ref> He also works on the open-source general distributed computing engine [[BOINC]], and designed levels for the iPhone video game [[Tap Tap Revenge]].
